SUMMARY:Yom HaShoah Interfaith Remembrance (Offsite)
DESCRIPTION:All are welcome to join the annual interfaith Yom HaShoah Holocaust Commemoration\, hosted by the Montclair Interfaith Clergy Association. \n  \nAs part of the service\, we will hear from Pamela Romanchuk\, granddaughter of four Holocaust survivors\, who will share her family’s stories of survival\, family\, legacy\, and the enduring strength of the Jewish People.
URL:https://www.unioncong.org/event/yom-hashoah-interfaith-remembrance-offsite/
LOCATION:Temple B’nai Keshet\, 99 S Fullerton Ave\, Montclair\, NJ\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:All Events,Featured Events
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Union Congregational Church
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260414T123000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260414T140000
DTSTAMP:20260410T225300
CREATED:20260123T203423Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260317T062454Z
UID:10002686-1776169800-1776175200@www.unioncong.org
SUMMARY:Bible Study (Guild Room)
DESCRIPTION:From Daytime Bible Study Leader Paul N:\nDuring Daytime Bible Study\, we discuss the Bible and books that analyze the Bible in depth. We also have fun and food. In 2024\, we studied Mark and screened films Sabbath and 1946: The Mistranslation That Shifted A Culture. We read books about Holy Week\, the Sabbath\, The Sermon On The Mount\, and Biblical women. All reference resources\, translations\, and interpretations are welcome. \nCurrent Book: “Who Stole My Bible? Reclaiming Scripture As A Handbook For Resisting Tyranny” by Rev. Jennifer Butler. \nPast Bible Study Books Have Included:\nSabbath As Resistance by Walter Brueggeman\nEntering The Passion Of Jesus by Amy-Jill Levine\nJesus’ Alternative Plan: The Sermon On The Mount by Richard Rohr
URL:https://www.unioncong.org/event/bible-study-guild-room-3-3/2026-04-14/
LOCATION:Guild Room
CATEGORIES:All Church Events,All Events,Featured Events,Small Groups
ORGANIZER;CN="Union Congregational Event":MAILTO:contact@unioncong.org
END:VEVENT
